  "prompt": "Who was the Guru of Guru Nanak Dev Ji?",
  "response": "Guru Nanak Dev Ji, the founder of Sikhism, is said to have had a spiritual experience that deeply influenced his beliefs and teachings. While Guru Nanak did not have a formal guru in the way that later Sikh Gurus did, he had a profound encounter with the Divine during a period of meditation. Some accounts describe this experience as a revelation from God, rather than a traditional guru-disciple relationship. \n\nIn Sikh tradition, it is understood that God or the divine truth is the ultimate \"Guru.\" This understanding emphasizes that the path to spiritual realization comes through a direct connection to the divine rather than through an intermediary. Thus, while there isn't a specific historical figure recognized as Guru Nanak's guru, his spiritual experiences and insights shaped his teachings and laid the foundation for Sikhism.",
